World War II, also known as the Second World War, began on September 1, 1939, and ended on September 2, 1945. The war involved most of the world's great powers, organized into two opposing military alliances: the Allies (mostly Britain, France, the Soviet Union, China, and the United States) and the Axis (mostly Germany, Italy, and Japan).
